---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Taiwan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/taiwan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Japan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/japan' },
  { title: 'South Korea for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-korea' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'taiwanFit', header: 'Taiwan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NT$10,500-15,000/mo', taiwanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NT$12,300-17,600/mo', taiwanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NT$9,500-13,500/mo', taiwanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NT$8,700-12,500/mo', taiwanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Taiwan NHI', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'Income-based', taiwanFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'NT$9,500-15,000', annual: 'NT$114,000-180,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'NT$13,000-19,900', annual: 'NT$156,000-238,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'NT$17,600-26,800', annual: 'NT$211,200-321,600' },
  { category: 'Taiwan Hospital (with NHI)', monthly: 'Minimal copay', annual: 'NT$100-500/visit' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'NT$2,000-8,000/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Taiwan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Taiwan. World-class healthcare, affordable NHI, Chinese culture, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Taiwan"
  subheadline="Taiwan offers world-class healthcare at affordable prices, Chinese culture with modern amenities, remarkable safety, and one of world best national health systems."
  heroImage="/images/countries/taiwan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Taiwan</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan offers exceptional value—world-class healthcare at very affordable prices, safety, efficiency, and rich Chinese culture. The National Health Insurance (NHI) system is consistently ranked among world best. For those seeking Asian modernity with Chinese heritage, Taiwan delivers.
  </p>

  <p>
    Taipei offers capital amenities with world-class healthcare. Taichung provides lower costs and pleasant weather. Kaohsiung has port city character and warmth. Tainan offers historic temples and culture. East coast provides natural beauty. Each region has distinct appeal.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> World-class; NHI ranked among best</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Mandarin; English limited</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> NT$45,000-100,000/month (~$1,400-3,100); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Subtropical; hot summers, mild winters</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Among world safest countries</li>
      <li><strong>Culture:</strong> Chinese heritage; democratic; progressive</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Taiwan Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan has excellent healthcare—NHI system consistently ranked among world best. Comprehensive coverage, minimal wait times, advanced technology, affordable costs. National Taiwan University Hospital, Taipei Veterans General, Chang Gung are world-class. Even small towns have good facilities.
  </p>

  <p>
    Residents can enroll in NHI after 6 months of legal residence. Coverage is comprehensive with minimal copays. International insurance provides supplement for premium services. Taiwan healthcare quality rivals any developed nation.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">NHI Excellence</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Taiwan NHI is consistently ranked among world top 5 healthcare systems. Universal coverage, low costs (premiums ~$25-50/month), comprehensive benefits, minimal copays. IC card system is efficient. World-class healthcare at fraction of Western costs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan has various visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Resident Visa (Retiree)</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with proof of financial means. Demonstrate NT$500,000+ (~$15,000) savings and income. Leads to Alien Resident Certificate (ARC). NHI eligible after 6 months.
  </p>

  <h3>Investment Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing NT$6M+ (~$185,000) in Taiwan. Provides residence and leads to NHI enrollment.
  </p>

  <h3>Gold Card</h3>
  <p>
    For professionals and high earners. 3-year residence and work rights. Popular among skilled retirees with expertise.
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free/Tourist</h3>
  <p>
    90-day visa-free for many nationalities. Extensions possible but not suitable for long-term retirement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Taiwan:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> NHI enrollment after 6 months mandatory</li>
    <li><strong>NHI:</strong> World-class coverage; very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Supplement for premium services if desired</li>
    <li><strong>First 6 months:</strong> Private coverage needed</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Taiwan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Taiwan NHI is excellent—many residents use NHI alone. International insurance provides supplement for VIP services, home country coverage, and first 6 months before NHI eligibility. NHI copays are so low that high coverage may not be necessary.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Taiwan, international coverage supplements world-class NHI:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Taiwan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Asia network, Taiwan hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Asia expertise, good Taiwan coverage</li>
    <li><strong>NHI:</strong> World-class coverage after 6-month wait</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage to supplement Taiwan excellent NHI.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Taiwan are moderate given excellent NHI:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NHI enrollment:</strong> After 6 months, provides excellent coverage</li>
    <li><strong>NHI alone:</strong> Many residents need nothing more</li>
    <li><strong>Supplement only:</strong> International for VIP/home country</li>
    <li><strong>Outside Taipei:</strong> Lower living costs, same healthcare quality</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American ABC, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Taiwanese heritage, $2,200/month pension. Taipei return.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Resident visa. NHI enrollment + Cigna Global for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> NHI ~NT$750 + Cigna ~NT$12,000/month. Cultural homecoming; world-class healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Tea Enthusiast, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,000/month pension. Taipei lifestyle, tea culture.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Gold Card. BUPA Global + NHI after 6 months.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~NT$14,000/month (~£380). Safe, modern; excellent healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Australian Digital Nomad, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> AUD 2,500/month pension. Kaohsiung, warmer climate.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Resident visa. Now Health first 6 months, then NHI.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~NT$10,500/month (~AUD 430). Affordable; efficient living.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Taiwan NHI really that good?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—consistently ranked top 5 globally. Universal coverage, comprehensive benefits, minimal copays (~$5-15), no wait times for most care. IC card system is efficient. Premiums are very low ($25-50/month based on income). Genuine world-class system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How is the language barrier?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—Mandarin is primary language. English less common than expected. Major hospitals have English services. Younger generation speaks more English. Learning basic Mandarin very helpful. Apps and translation tools help daily life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Taiwan affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—cheaper than Japan/Korea, more expensive than Southeast Asia. Taipei is pricier; southern cities more affordable. Public transit excellent. Healthcare incredibly affordable with NHI. $1,800-3,000/month for comfortable living.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about cross-strait tensions?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Status quo persists—daily life is completely normal. Taiwan is very safe with low crime. Most expats feel secure. Situation monitored but not affecting daily life. Many long-term residents. Worth researching but not immediate concern for most.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Taiwan coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Taiwan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
